{"word":"H5012 - נָבָא - nâbâʼ - naw-baw' - Prophesy","slug":"H5012","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">נָבָא</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>nâbâʼ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>naw-baw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Prophesy"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E0;&#x05D1;&#x05D0; - na&#x0302;ba&#x0302;'</b> - <i>naw-baw'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>prophesy</i>, that is, speak (or sing) by inspiration (in prediction or simple discourse): - prophesy (-ing) make self a prophet."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H5016\">H5016</a>, <a href=\"#/H5030\">H5030</a>, <a href=\"#/H5031\">H5031</a>"}]}